Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.96,0:01:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.83,0:01:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Hail Nebo, Ishtar,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.38,0:01:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and Marduk—greatest god of all!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.01,0:01:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yah!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.41,0:02:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Call the wise men.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.87,0:02:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Call the wise men!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.38,0:02:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t know what that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.80,0:02:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn’t appear to be an omen.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.84,0:02:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s nothing in the books, is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.34,0:02:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Are these all the wise men?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.93,0:02:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The best in the kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.72,0:02:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, I need to speak to the king!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.35,0:02:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The queen mother, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.02,0:02:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,O king, may you live on forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.32,0:02:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s a man in your kingdom
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.32,0:02:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,who has the spirit of the holy gods.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.95,0:02:59.99,Default,,0,0,0,,He will tell you the interpretation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.83,0:03:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is this man?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.95,0:03:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.66,0:03:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.33,0:03:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Who’s Daniel?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.59,0:03:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you Daniel?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.26,0:03:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I am, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.89,0:04:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve heard concerning you
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.93,0:04:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,that you’re able to provide interpretations.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.06,0:04:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if you are able to read the writing
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.77,0:04:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and make its interpretation known to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.56,0:04:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you will be clothed with purple,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.15,0:04:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,a gold necklace will be placed around your neck,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.74,0:04:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and you will rule as the third one in the kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.66,0:04:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You may keep your gifts.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.99,0:04:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Give your presents to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.79,0:04:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,However, I will read the writing to the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.71,0:04:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The Most High God granted to Nebuchadnezzar
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.29,0:04:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the kingdom and greatness
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.80,0:04:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and honor and majesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.38,0:04:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But when his heart became haughty,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.68,0:04:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,he was brought down from the throne of his kingdom
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.01,0:04:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and his dignity was taken away.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.65,0:04:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But you, Belshazzar—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.82,0:04:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You have not humbled your heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.40,0:05:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,although you knew all of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.24,0:05:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.87,0:05:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you exalted yourself against the Lord of the heavens.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.20,0:05:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You had them bring you the vessels of His house.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.17,0:05:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you and your nobles,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.17,0:05:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,your concubines and secondary wives
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.50,0:05:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,drank wine from them
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.51,0:05:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and praised the gods of silver and gold
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.55,0:05:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,—gods who see nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.18,0:05:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and hear nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.64,0:05:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and know nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.90,0:05:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But you’ve not glorified the God
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.65,0:05:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,in whose hand is your breath
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.36,0:05:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and all your ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.82,0:05:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So the hand was sent from Him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.62,0:05:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the interpretation of the words:
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.08,0:05:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,MENE:
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.42,0:06:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,God has numbered the days of your kingdom
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.63,0:06:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and brought it to an end.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.89,0:06:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,TEKEL:
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.36,0:06:21.37,Default,,0,0,0,,You have been weighed in the balances
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.36,0:06:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and found lacking.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.33,0:06:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,PERES:
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.50,0:06:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Your kingdom has been divided
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.67,0:06:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and given to the Medes
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.75,0:06:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Persians.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.42,0:07:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,King Darius, this is Daniel
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.71,0:07:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,—a Jew taken captive by the Babylonians.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.89,0:07:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you interpret the handwriting from the gods?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.68,0:07:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.27,0:07:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Not me, O king
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.77,0:07:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,—my God—
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.98,0:07:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the God of Israel.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.36,0:07:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We could use a satrap
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.57,0:07:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,who understands the captives.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.95,0:07:50.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I confess, a satrap
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.95,0:07:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,is not as prominent a position
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.66,0:07:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,as Belshazzar granted you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.37,0:07:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord, Daniel refused
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.91,0:08:00.83,Default,,0,0,0,,every gift and honor Belshazzar offered him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.05,0:08:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,A man without a price.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.80,0:08:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We don’t need you as a satrap
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.22,0:08:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,—we need you over them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.81,0:08:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Tura,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.35,0:08:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,pronounce Daniel’s appointment
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.35,0:08:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout the kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.23,0:08:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I want those stealing from the treasury to know
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.11,0:08:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,that they will now be held accountable.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.39,0:08:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.72,0:08:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you’ll make a fine high official.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.23,0:09:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Only with Jehovah’s help.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.75,0:09:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is the land tax so high?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.18,0:09:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Another revolt?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.60,0:09:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,This is far more troubling.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.85,0:09:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I just collected the land tax from an administrator.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.35,0:09:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Did he pay?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.19,0:09:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, but he refuses to give us “our fees.”
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.98,0:09:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve had the same problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.40,0:09:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re calling anything more than the tax extortion.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.36,0:09:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s changed?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.03,0:09:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.37,0:09:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you offered him anything
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.20,0:10:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,to make him more reasonable?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.91,0:10:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,He won’t take a shekel of silver.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.66,0:10:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel claims that what he receives
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.37,0:10:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,is more than enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.59,0:10:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t be so naive!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.59,0:10:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s putting on a show of integrity for the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.72,0:10:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It won’t last.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.30,0:10:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Darius will tire of him soon enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.56,0:10:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,There seems to be a discrepancy in the taxes
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.56,0:10:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,due the treasury, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.73,0:10:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re brave to say that here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.78,0:10:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I know it’s hard to hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.78,0:10:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We will review the evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.16,0:10:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel, your time here has given you much wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.87,0:10:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,How long have you been here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.29,0:10:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 70 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.54,0:10:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Share more with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.13,0:10:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me about the dreams
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.63,0:10:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,you interpreted for Nebuchadnezzar.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.63,0:10:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Interpretations belong to my God,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.30,0:10:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.80,0:10:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,He revealed the dreams to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.19,0:11:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Have I really been in Babylon over 70 years?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.12,0:11:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeremiah’s prophecy!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.97,0:11:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“When 70 years have been fulfilled,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.97,0:11:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,“I will call to account the king of Babylon
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.56,0:11:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and that nation for their error.”
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.69,0:11:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Belshazzar’s death
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.36,0:11:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,—it’s been fulfilled!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.96,0:12:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What does this mean for God’s people?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.28,0:12:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,“When 70 years at Babylon are fulfilled,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.11,0:12:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,“I will turn my attention to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.95,0:12:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“and I will make good my promise
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.50,0:12:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,by bringing you back to this place.”
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.21,0:12:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Judah!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.34,0:13:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I must approach Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.35,0:13:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to confess the sin of my people.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.52,0:13:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,O Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.07,0:13:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,do hear,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.69,0:13:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,do forgive.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.70,0:13:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,O Jehovah, do pay attention and act.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.58,0:13:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not delay, for your own sake,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.46,0:13:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,O my God.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.67,0:13:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,O Daniel,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.17,0:13:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,now I have come to give you insight
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.55,0:13:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.97,0:13:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,When you began your entreaty,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.14,0:13:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the word went out,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.77,0:13:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and I have come to report it to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.60,0:13:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,There are 70 weeks that have been determined
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.31,0:13:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,for your people and your holy city
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.36,0:14:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to terminate the transgression,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.36,0:14:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,to finish off sin.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.62,0:14:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel, Azarel and Hannah are here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.42,0:14:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, Daniel.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.21,0:14:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s so good to see you!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.75,0:14:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Epher, come sit with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.59,0:14:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I have good news!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.51,0:14:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s the good news?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.10,0:14:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah has long told us
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.77,0:14:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that we will return to Judah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.10,0:14:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I looked again at Jeremiah’s prophecy:
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.44,0:14:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,“This is what Jehovah says,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.99,0:14:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘When 70 years at Babylon are fulfilled, . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.20,0:14:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘I will make good my promise
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.83,0:14:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,by bringing you back to this place.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.37,0:14:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,“Seventy years.”
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.42,0:15:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That means God’s people will return soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.04,0:15:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you be sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.88,0:15:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah sent an angel to tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.14,0:15:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,An angel?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.76,0:15:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He said that the city
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.14,0:15:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and its temple will be rebuilt,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.69,0:15:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Messiah will finally come!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.86,0:15:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You will get to see the temple rebuilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.40,0:15:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But won’t it be dangerous?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.32,0:15:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is eager
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.83,0:15:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,to fulfill the needs of his people.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.29,0:15:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,He told Isaiah
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.79,0:15:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that we ‘won’t bear children for distress,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.88,0:15:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,‘for they’re the offspring
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.17,0:15:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,made up of those blessed by Jehovah.’
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.72,0:15:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And if Jehovah says it,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.22,0:15:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s as good as done!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.51,0:15:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But isn’t the land desolate?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.43,0:15:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s why we’ll need skilled builders
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.89,0:15:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,for the restoration work.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.85,0:16:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Does this mean you’ll return to Judah?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.49,0:16:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I sure hope so.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.12,0:16:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Have a team of workers maintain the roads.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.58,0:16:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, conditions will only worsen
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.62,0:16:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,during the rainy season.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.59,0:16:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Tura, see that it’s done.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.88,0:16:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,How is it that you know so much?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.09,0:16:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I can’t take credit, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.01,0:16:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I just . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.01,0:16:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We have many great men
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.01,0:16:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,who provide the information we need, O king.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.23,0:16:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.98,0:16:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,about that satrap in Susa.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.27,0:16:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Should he be replaced?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.07,0:16:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,My men have thoroughly investigated,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.95,0:16:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and the satrap has been diverting palace money
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.16,0:16:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,to his own pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.24,0:16:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s—that’s impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.91,0:16:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn’t he your nephew, Otanes?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.16,0:17:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed, and I can vouch for his integrity!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.37,0:17:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,There must be some mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.63,0:17:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,How can Daniel know his character as I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.80,0:17:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I will speak with him and resolve the matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.84,0:17:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We Medes and Persians
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.43,0:17:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,are not as intolerant as these Jews.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.06,0:17:20.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sure we can fix this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.89,0:17:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well. Settle it quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.77,0:17:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That will be all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.23,0:18:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord, I’m so sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.15,0:18:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You have guests.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.45,0:18:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,All you Jews do is pray.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.62,0:18:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I could not serve the king
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.63,0:18:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the way I do without God’s help.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.67,0:18:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Serve the king
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.67,0:18:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,by intimidating satraps?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.76,0:18:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve only done what I should.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.76,0:18:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,An outsider has no place telling us
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.97,0:18:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,how to conduct business.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.47,0:18:43.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I act in the king’s interests.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.02,0:18:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve heard how you acted
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.40,0:18:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,in Nebuchadnezzar’s interests.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.15,0:18:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You made him go insane.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.94,0:18:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a message from Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.99,0:18:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Call it what you will,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.07,0:18:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,but do not interfere with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.62,0:19:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,If it seemed easy
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.50,0:19:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to remove a satrap,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.25,0:19:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,think of how much easier it will be
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.54,0:19:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,to get rid of an old Jew.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.24,0:19:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s an honor to be with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.99,0:19:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know why I summoned you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.45,0:19:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,No, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.74,0:19:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That satrap whose dismissal Daniel recommended
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.71,0:19:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,—what’s become of him?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.04,0:19:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we thoroughly investigated the matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.63,0:19:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Was there negligence?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.92,0:19:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,None.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.09,0:19:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Any omission of duty?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.46,0:19:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.80,0:20:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,All taxes due the treasury have come to the treasury?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.09,0:20:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Every shekel of gold and quart (1.08 L) of beer
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.97,0:20:04.35,Default,,0,0,0,,are accounted for.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.68,0:20:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel reached a different conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.44,0:20:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, Daniel—
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.48,0:20:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He served the Babylonian kings well, but . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.40,0:20:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,he’s so old!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.53,0:20:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What Otanes means is,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.03,0:20:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,at Daniel’s age, how reliable is his judgment?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.61,0:20:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,His ideas are outdated.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.58,0:20:25.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, he is a Jew.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.37,0:20:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Katu, we are tolerant of all peoples.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.37,0:20:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, of course. That’s my point.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.71,0:20:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel, we were just talking about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.92,0:20:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You were right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.17,0:20:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s been a revolt in Susa.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.55,0:20:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,They demand a new satrap
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.09,0:20:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,—one who doesn’t steal from them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.01,0:20:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But my lord, surely . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.60,0:20:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.02,0:20:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I sent my own inspectors—men I trust!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.27,0:20:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel, you’ve distinguished yourself over these men.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.90,0:21:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine what I could do if you were my prime minister.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.75,0:21:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps we could approach the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.08,0:21:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s no use.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.71,0:21:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel’s manipulating him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.71,0:21:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We need an accusation against Daniel
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.75,0:21:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,—something that Darius can’t ignore.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.76,0:21:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But no one has accused him of anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.47,0:21:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.51,0:21:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Assemble a team to comb through our laws.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.85,0:21:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Surely he’s violated something.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.10,0:21:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.72,0:21:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Interview merchants, inspectors, officials
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.94,0:21:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,—whoever will make an accusation against him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.10,0:21:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Assure the accuser
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.52,0:21:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,he will be generously rewarded.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.44,0:21:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We have the Babylonian records.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.61,0:21:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Search for any scandal that might implicate him.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.39,0:22:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,There is nothing in the records.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.93,0:22:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.35,0:22:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a shekel of silver is missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.19,0:22:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, when Daniel gets involved,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.53,0:22:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,corruption and loss go down.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.36,0:22:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep searching.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.87,0:22:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,No one will speak against him.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.21,0:22:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,They all love him,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.38,0:22:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and he has the king’s trust.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.39,0:22:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually, the foreign merchants are ignored
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.06,0:22:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,when they experience theft.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.31,0:22:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,However, Daniel stands up for them
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.64,0:22:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and investigates.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.48,0:23:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,He has thieves return whatever was stolen.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.82,0:23:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Even his friends are spotless.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.03,0:23:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Nebuchadnezzar once forbade anyone
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.03,0:23:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to speak against their God.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.03,0:23:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Supposedly,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.08,0:23:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,this “Jehovah” saved them from the furnace
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.79,0:23:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,when they refused to worship a Babylonian god.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.46,0:23:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Jews won’t worship other gods?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.30,0:23:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So it would seem.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.42,0:23:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you’ve solved our problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.55,0:23:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Katu, Otanes, what favor do you seek?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.64,0:23:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,O King Darius, may you live on forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.48,0:23:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,This Babylon of which you are king
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.77,0:23:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,is mighty but diverse.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.77,0:23:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,There are Babylonians, Egyptians, Greeks, and others.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.24,0:23:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Otanes, I know these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.20,0:23:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You are the rightful king
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.20,0:23:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,but also a foreigner and a newcomer.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.54,0:23:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The people must adapt,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.50,0:23:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,or the kingdom could become unstable.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.79,0:23:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you suggest?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.29,0:24:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,All royal officials,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.30,0:24:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,prefects, satraps,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.05,0:24:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,high royal officers, and governors
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.51,0:24:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,have consulted together to establish a royal decree
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.72,0:24:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and to enforce a ban
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.14,0:24:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,that for 30 days, whoever makes a petition
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.06,0:24:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,to any god or man
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.94,0:24:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,except to you, O king,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.02,0:24:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,should be thrown into the lions’ pit.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.98,0:24:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The people are not above rebellion.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.82,0:24:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Look what happened in Susa.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.99,0:24:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, O king,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.66,0:24:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,may you establish the decree and sign it
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.71,0:24:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,so that it cannot be changed,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.75,0:24:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,according to the law of the Medes and the Persians,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.38,0:24:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,which cannot be annulled.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.31,0:24:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,At this time,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.81,0:25:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,our empire experiences peace and prosperity
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.52,0:25:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,unlike ever seen before.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.61,0:25:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The recent acts of defiance in Susa,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.69,0:25:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,along with similar acts by small groups of radicals,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.03,0:25:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,seek to undermine
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.32,0:25:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,our way of life
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.33,0:25:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,—a way of life we will sacrifice for nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.25,0:25:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,In honor of the glorious freedom
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.38,0:25:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,so kindly granted by the empire
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.09,0:25:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and as a reminder of its sovereignty,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.26,0:25:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I, Darius the Mede,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.38,0:25:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,make this decree:
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.43,0:25:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,For 30 days, anyone
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.01,0:25:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,who makes a petition to any god or man,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.73,0:25:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,except to the king,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.23,0:25:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,should be thrown into the lions’ pit.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.88,0:26:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re not going home to pray, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.22,0:26:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Azarel,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.43,0:26:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,you know me,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.98,0:26:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and so do my enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.60,0:26:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I pray at my window three times a day,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.44,0:26:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.23,0:26:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If I even appear to compromise,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.70,0:26:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,what would they think?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.41,0:26:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That you stopped praying altogether.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.20,0:26:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Or even worse,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.50,0:26:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that I’d trade my worship for my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.05,0:26:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I know Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.17,0:26:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And if I trust him,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.13,0:26:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,he’ll reward me.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.34,0:26:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t know how,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.35,0:27:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,but he will.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.44,0:27:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Pray that I keep my faith
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.40,0:27:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,—that we all keep our faith—
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.24,0:27:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter how this ends.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.84,0:27:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I have something for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.89,0:27:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Dinner’s ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.20,0:28:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jehovah is my light
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.29,0:28:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,“and my salvation.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.29,0:28:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Whom should I fear?”
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.51,0:28:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“Hear me, O Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.43,0:28:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,“when I cry out.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.06,0:28:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,“Show me favor
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.03,0:28:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“and answer me.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.16,0:28:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,“Your face, O Jehovah, I will seek to find.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.12,0:28:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,“[For] you are my helper;
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.42,0:28:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,“do not forsake me 
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.63,0:28:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“or leave me,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.72,0:29:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,my God of salvation.”
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.54,0:30:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,O king, may you live on forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.59,0:30:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you not sign a ban
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.21,0:30:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,stating that for 30 days any man
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.59,0:30:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,who makes a petition to any god or man
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.18,0:30:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,—except to you, O king—
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.39,0:30:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,should be thrown into the lions’ pit?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.39,0:30:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, the matter is well-established
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.39,0:30:34.43,Default,,0,0,0,,according to the law of the Medes and the Persians.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.44,0:30:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s your business?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.48,0:30:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel, who is of the exiles of Judah,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.82,0:30:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,has paid no regard to you, O king,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.82,0:30:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,nor to the ban that you signed.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.70,0:30:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But three times a day,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.91,0:30:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,he is praying.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.38,0:31:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.89,0:31:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It can’t be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.35,0:31:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.02,0:31:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn’t even try to deny it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.81,0:31:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Were there witnesses?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.94,0:31:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,All five of us, my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.53,0:31:24.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We can attest to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.36,0:31:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But he is old.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.32,0:31:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Does he know what he’s doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.32,0:31:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,As a high official,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.33,0:31:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,surely he understands what it means
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.54,0:31:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to obey the king.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.38,0:31:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me be.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.38,0:31:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Should we arrest Daniel?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.96,0:31:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave the matter to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.31,0:32:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel should indeed be made an example of.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.94,0:32:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll remove him from his post
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.98,0:32:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and expel him from the city tomorrow morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.32,0:32:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord . . . 
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.36,0:32:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,All will learn that our laws must be obeyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.45,0:32:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But the law actually states that the accused
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.24,0:32:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,would be “thrown into the lions’ pit,” my lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.58,0:32:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I see what you’re doing!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.79,0:33:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you no shame?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.79,0:33:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The law of the Medes and the Persians
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.55,0:33:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,is that any ban or decree that the king establishes
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.38,0:33:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot be changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.43,0:33:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,We only wish the king to receive the honor
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.80,0:33:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,he deserves.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.36,0:33:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Take him to the pit.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.35,0:36:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Your God, whom you are continually serving,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.14,0:36:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,will rescue you.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.62,0:36:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Remove the stone!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.96,0:36:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.59,0:36:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.01,0:36:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,O king, may you live on forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.56,0:36:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,He lives!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.64,0:36:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Bring him up!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.44,0:36:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,My God sent his angel
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.94,0:36:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and shut the mouths of the lions,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.49,0:37:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and they have not harmed me,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.95,0:37:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,for I was found innocent before him;
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.79,0:37:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,nor have I done any wrong to you, O king.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.34,0:37:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Armenia is mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.43,0:37:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel let them off too easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.05,0:37:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We need their exceptional horses for our cavalry
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.14,0:37:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and a few for myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.90,0:37:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine, you take Armenia.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.02,0:37:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I have my eye on Bactria and its precious stones.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.61,0:37:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Must you divide up Daniel’s kingdom now?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.87,0:37:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Check the back room!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.25,0:37:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the meaning of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.17,0:37:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You are being arrested
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.63,0:37:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,for crimes against Darius the king!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.46,0:38:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The king ordered Daniel’s arrest, not ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.30,0:38:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel was arrested
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.76,0:38:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and lifted from the pit this morning
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.85,0:38:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,—unharmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.97,0:38:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It can’t be!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.52,0:38:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The lions must have already been fed.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.94,0:38:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps they were ill.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.15,0:38:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The lions were ill?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.65,0:38:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Not hungry?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.62,0:38:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Throw them and their families into the pit,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.62,0:38:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,where they can test their theories.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.50,0:38:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,No! Darius!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.59,0:38:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t do this! I served you!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.63,0:38:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,No! Don’t do this!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.09,0:38:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I served you!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.72,0:38:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,No! Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.18,0:38:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.06,0:38:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I am issuing an order
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.85,0:38:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,that in every domain of my kingdom,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.06,0:38:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,people are to tremble in fear
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.19,0:38:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,before the God of Daniel.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.86,0:39:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,For he is the living God, and he endures forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.78,0:39:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,His kingdom will never be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.78,0:39:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“He rescues,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.03,0:39:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“saves, and performs signs and wonders
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.74,0:39:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,“in the heavens and on the earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.29,0:39:15.09,Default,,0,0,0,,for he rescued Daniel from the paw of the lions.”
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.08,0:39:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Darius wrote that?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.71,0:39:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s sending it to all of his subjects.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.88,0:39:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We were so worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.17,0:39:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Were you scared?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.30,0:39:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I was very scared,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.30,0:39:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,but Jehovah helps us when we’re scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.10,0:39:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re scared of going to Jerusalem.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.02,0:39:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Epher!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.19,0:39:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re still thinking about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.90,0:39:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,How about you? Are you going back?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.32,0:39:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The king says we’re all allowed to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.41,0:39:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I’d love to go home,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.63,0:40:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,but
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.97,0:40:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it’s too late for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.57,0:40:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I don’t want to go either.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.61,0:40:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no, no, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.65,0:40:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.33,0:40:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,If you go,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.37,0:40:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,you’ll see a better city than the one I left.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.17,0:40:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll see prophecies fulfilled,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.88,0:40:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,a city full of people worshipping Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.97,0:40:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and a new temple
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.14,0:40:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,—the most beautiful building on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.79,0:41:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you see our old neighbor at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.71,0:41:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I didn’t him at all today.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.05,0:41:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw our neighbor Eli the other day.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.50,0:42:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay close to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.51,0:42:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You will be blessed.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.52,0:42:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,“One thing
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.52,0:42:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,“I have asked from Jehovah . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.95,0:42:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,“that I might dwell
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.75,0:42:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,“in the house of Jehovah all the days of my life,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.05,0:43:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,“to gaze
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.10,0:43:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,“upon the pleasantness of Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.69,0:43:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,“and to look
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.11,0:43:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,“with appreciation
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.95,0:43:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,on his temple.”
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.93,0:44:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Daniel, you need to rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.32,0:45:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,O Daniel, you very precious man.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.86,0:45:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I have been sent to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.99,0:45:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not be afraid, Daniel.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.37,0:45:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Your words have been heard from the first day
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.96,0:45:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,you gave your heart to understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.04,0:45:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and humbling yourself before your God.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.59,0:45:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I have come to make you understand
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.59,0:45:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,what will befall your people
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.59,0:45:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,in the final part of the days.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.59,0:45:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.30,0:45:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s no breath left in me.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.43,0:45:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not be afraid, O very precious man.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.85,0:45:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,May you have peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.39,0:45:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Be strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.73,0:45:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Be strong!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.87,0:46:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Let my lord speak,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.24,0:46:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,for you have strengthened me.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.58,0:46:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I will tell you the things recorded
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.79,0:46:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,in the writings of truth:
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.79,0:46:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.00,0:46:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,“Three more kings will stand up for Persia,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.71,0:46:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“and the fourth one will amass greater riches
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.30,0:46:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,than all others.”
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.74,0:46:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,O my lord,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.57,0:46:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,what will be the outcome of these things?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.70,0:46:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Happy is the one who keeps in expectation.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.33,0:46:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Go on to the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.12,0:46:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You will rest,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.83,0:46:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,but you will stand up for your lot
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.84,0:46:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,at the end of the days.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.94,0:47:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,If we eat those foods, we’ll disobey our God.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.28,0:47:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You fear your God?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.28,0:47:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.49,0:47:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Interpretations belong to my God, Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.16,0:47:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that he will reveal it to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.33,0:47:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.00,0:47:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,is eager to fulfill the needs of his people.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.14,0:47:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I know Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.81,0:47:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And if I trust him,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.27,0:48:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,he’ll reward me.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.12,0:48:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t know how,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.34,0:48:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,but he will.
